											<p><em>Attend our free webinar July 12 and discover SEO, social media and content tactics to boost your brand’s online visibility. <a>Register Now  »</a></em></p>

										
					<p>In this edition of #3minthursdays, Savannah Sanchez, digital content director at California-based <a>7Twelve Marketing</a>, takes you through the ins and outs of <a>Snapchat</a> marketing. She shares tips on sending your first snaps, how the platform compares to "the other guys" and how to grow your follower base.</p><p>With Snapchat, users can send photos and videos to each other, and then they delete automatically from the platform. And to date, the Snapchat community -- which includes businesses trying to promote their brands -- has shared over a billion snaps!</p><p>"In contrast, on <a>Instagram</a>, brands often try to pick a perfect image or video to post," Sanchez says in this video. "They can spend hours selecting the right shot and editing the image they're after. While it's important to keep up quality, it's not as serious on Snapchat. That's because the stakes are much lower."</p><p>Sanchez recommends that businesses should use Snapchat to let their audience see behind-the-scenes action and real-life interactions. It's also important to keep your snaps upbeat and genuine. </p><p>Click play to learn more best-practice techniques for this relaxed social-media platform -- and get snapping!</p><p></p><p><em>The <a>Entrepreneur Network</a> is a global movement of creative, energetic and inspired video creators sharing their ideas, experience and vision for the next generation of business founders and owners. We provide expertise and opportunities to accelerate brand growth and effectively monetize video and audio content distributed across all digital platforms for the business genre.</em></p><p><em> to become a part of this growing video network.</em></p>				
				
